CatDescriptText: Reed Jackson, news dealer, Homewood was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 9, 1960, pg. A1 with question: "Whom do you think the Democratic and the Republican parties will choose for their respective presidential candidates? Why?" Answer reads: "The Democrats will choose Johnson, because he is a good man and well known. And these are the same reasons that the Republicans will choose Nixon."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Reed Jackson wearing hat and dark cardigan, standing in front of grocery store window displaying petroleum jelly
